label.value: Hepatitis A virus-Typhoid vaccine foreign to USA

definition.value: A vaccine to protect individuals against infections caused by hepatitis A virus and typhoid fever bacteria.
This term was used by the USA VAERS system to indicate the source, which is foreign to USA here, of the vaccine.
